OL,3,CEx-service user reflects on
OL,4,C'absolutely crucial' work by Leeds
OL,5,CWomen's Aid
OL,7,F"We were just living in extreme
OL,8,Fpoverty, and he was going to sell
OL,9,Feverything in the house. And so I just
OL,10,Fthought enough was enough. I packed up
OL,11,Feverything that I had, and contacted
OL,12,FLWA."
OL,14,FNow working for LWA, Clare said
OL,15,Fservices are on offer are "broader".
