OL,3,CEx-service user reflects on
OL,4,C'absolutely crucial' work by Leeds
OL,5,CWomen's Aid
OL,7,F"I think it's a really trauma-informed
OL,8,Fservice, and there's a lot of focus on
OL,9,Fsupporting the children and the wider
OL,10,Ffamily. I think before it was just
OL,11,Fabout rescuing women from the
OL,12,Fsituation and giving them a home.
OL,13,FWhereas now I just feel that our
OL,14,Fservices are a lot broader.
OL,16,F"We provide opportunities for the
OL,17,Fchildren to recover from the impact
OL,18,Fthat domestic abuse has had on them,
OL,19,Fas well as the women. So it's that
OL,20,Fwider family support that I really
OL,21,Fthink we do well now.
