OL,3,CEx-service user reflects on
OL,4,C'absolutely crucial' work by Leeds
OL,5,CWomen's Aid
OL,7,F"It's absolutely crucial that they
OL,8,Ffeel safe, they feel supported, and
OL,9,Falso that they're on a journey of self-
OL,10,Fdiscovery and understanding that what
OL,11,Fhappened to them wasn't their fault.
OL,13,F"Here we can help them heal, and
OL,14,Fprepare for an independent future with
OL,15,Fthe children."
OL,17,FReflecting on Christmas, Clare said:
OL,18,F"I think the number of women needing
OL,19,Four services increase over Christmas
OL,20,Fjust because there's an intense
OL,21,Fpressure on families."
